    Fix script portability and password handling (#3)
    
    Four issues surfaced in the v1.0.1 review that aren't user-facing in the
    manifest sense but break behavior in real use:
    
    1. exit -> return. Public scripts are dot-sourced by toolkit(); 'exit'
       terminated the user's PowerShell session instead of the script.
       Replaced 8 sites across get-guestaudit, get-groupmembers, get-userreport,
       set-userlicence, and offboard-user.
    
    2. offboard-user used [System.Web.Security.Membership]::GeneratePassword,
       which isn't available on PowerShell 7 (System.Web is a Framework-only
       assembly). Replaced with a portable generator built on
       RandomNumberGenerator that guarantees one of each M365 complexity class
       (upper, lower, digit, symbol) and shuffles via Fisher-Yates.
    
    3. offboard-user log claimed "New password logged in export" but the
       generated password was never actually written to the CSV. The Notes
       column now contains the password, matching the documented behavior.
    
    4. new-user accepted the initial password via plain Read-Host and echoed
       it in the trailing summary, leaving it in scrollback. Now reads as
       SecureString, converts to plain only at the New-MgUser call site, and
       clears the local copy in a finally block. Summary line shows
       "(set - not echoed)".
    
    CHANGELOG [Unreleased] updated. No version bump on this commit; will
    roll into the next dated release.

