    Add disable-autocalevents and inherit-permissions
    
    Two of the originally-promised commands that need real care, brought back
    from the "Planned" list:
    
    disable-autocalevents â€” tenant-wide Outlook 'Events from email' kill.
    Iterates every UserMailbox and SharedMailbox via Get-Mailbox, calls
    Set-MailboxCalendarConfiguration -EventsFromEmailEnabled $false on each.
    Because this affects an entire tenant the script forces the operator to
    type the primary verified domain before doing anything; a typo aborts.
    Already-disabled mailboxes are recorded as SKIPPED so re-runs are cheap.
    CSV log lands on the operator's Desktop with per-mailbox status.
    
    inherit-permissions â€” NTFS ACL reset. Re-enables inheritance on a folder
    via SetAccessRuleProtection($false, $true). The 'preserveInheritance' arg
    is set to $true so the folder doesn't briefly lose access during the
    transition. After inheritance is on, the operator is asked separately
    whether to strip the explicit (non-inherited) ACEs that remain. Pure
    local â€” no Graph or Exchange dependency. Includes the takeown hint in
    the failure path because permission errors here usually mean ownership.
    
    Manifest, toolkit() menu, README all updated. CHANGELOG entry under
    [Unreleased]. Two entries removed from the README "Planned" list.

